The paper deals with the design of the channel part of a digital communication system, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of Huffman codes, which is a topic related to data structures (cs.DS) and coding theory (cs.CC). The paper proposes a method for permuting the codewords of a Huffman code, which is a topic related to optimization (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
